BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ak9KxdWmYC6AYGrGCkPop
SUMMARY:Ribbon Cutting Celebration: Issaquah Improv School & Clown Garage
DTSTAMP:20260324T020908Z
DTSTART:20260325T110000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us as we officially welcome the Unexpected Productions Imp
	rov School and Clown Garage to Issaquah! On Wednesday\\\, March 25\\\, at 
	11:00 AM\\\, Mayor Mark Mullet will lead a ceremonial ribbon-cutting to ma
	rk the opening of this exciting new creative space dedicated to laughter\\
	\, play\\\, and fearless creativity.\\nPresented in partnership with the I
	ssaquah Chamber of Commerce\\\, this event celebrates the launch of a new 
	hub for training in improv\\\, clown\\\, and physical comedy on the Eastsi
	de. The school will offer classes\\\, workshops\\\, and performances desig
	ned to build confidence\\\, creativity\\\, communication skills\\\, and co
	mmunity.\\nAfter the ribbon-cutting\\\, stay to celebrate with light refre
	shments\\\, conversation\\\, and a chance to explore the new space\\\, mee
	t instructors\\\, and learn more about upcoming classes and programs.\\nWh
	ether you’re an artist\\\, educator\\\, student\\\, or simply curious abou
	t improv\\\, we invite you to come celebrate this exciting new chapter for
	 the Issaquah arts community.\\nCome meet your neighbors\\\, take a look i
	nside\\\, and help us cut the ribbon on a new home for creativity in Issaq
	uah.\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/ribbon-cutting-celebra
	tion-issaquah-improv-school-clown-garage/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/ribbon-cutting-celebration-
	issaquah-improv-school-clown-garage/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions Improv School ISSAQUAH/EASTSIDE\\\, 1315 NW
	 Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98108\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
